## Common Pitfalls to Avoid
- **Startup cold start**: Need `ATR_PERIOD` candles before regime is reliable — default to MEDIUM (safe) until warmed up
- **Threshold flapping**: Without `REGIME_CONFIRM_BARS`, the regime will flip back and forth on borderline ATR values, causing noisy entry/exit
- **Using raw ATR instead of ATR_PCT**: Raw ATR is not comparable across price levels — always normalize as % of price
- **Bypassing in "obvious" conditions**: Never hardcode regime overrides — the filter exists precisely for moments you think you know better
- **Forgetting mid-trade checks**: Regime can change while you're in a position — always re-check on each candle close

